By a vote of 366-34 with one lawmaker voting present, the House has overwhelmingly passed a bill that averts a government shutdown hours before the government runs out of funding. Speaker Mike Johnson (R-Louisiana) said earlier Friday that the new spending plan does not include President-elect Donald Trump’s demand to suspend the debt limit. The legislation would extend current fiscal levels until mid-March, provide $110 billion in relief to help natural-disaster survivors and aid farmers, and grant an extension for the farm bill, which must be reauthorized. The bill now goes to the Senate.

The U.S. finally got a national bird. Government websites called bald eagles the national bird. Textbooks and newspaper articles agreed. But when Preston Cook searched high and low for any official documentation cementing the bird’s status, he found nothing. Flabbergasted, in 2011 he wrote to his senator — the late Dianne Feinstein, a Democrat from California — asking if her staff could investigate this mystery at the National Archives. “It turns out that the documentation wasn’t missing — it didn’t exist. We’ve never had a national bird,” Cook told The Washington Post. “The senator sent me back a letter saying it’s assumed to be our national bird, but it has never been declared our national bird.” On Monday, Congress made it official. The bald eagle will become the national bird after 248 years. Caption from article by Maria Luisa Paul.

Where did we get syphilis? In a study published Wednesday in the journal Nature, an international team studied ancient DNA harvested from lesion-ridden bones or teeth of five people who lived in Peru, Chile, Argentina and Mexico either before or around the time of Columbus. They found that early versions of the microbe, Treponema pallidum, that causes syphilis and related diseases were already diverse and widespread. Their analysis suggests that syphilis emerged in the Americas within the last 8,000 years and spread across the globe fueled by European colonization. “The syphilis debate was a big one, and it was a very emotional one ... a famous paleopathologist described it as one of the most enigmatic questions in science,” said Kirsten Bos, group leader for molecular paleopathology at the Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology and one of the leaders of the work. She argued the new evidence would settle the matter. “It’s a very clear slam dunk: Okay, this clearly came from the Americas.” Several outside researchers agreed the study provides valuable new evidence strongly suggesting an American origin for syphilis, but added that it wouldn’t close the debate. Understanding the differences between the subspecies that cause these different, but related, diseases is a key question for scientists trying to understand these diseases today. Caption from article by Carolyn Y. Johnson.

FTC MAKES sellers REVEAL “junk fees" The Federal Trade Commission on Tuesday issued long-awaited rules requiring companies to display the full price of a hotel room, concert ticket or sporting event up front to customers, rather than hiding any extra charges — often called “junk fees” — until the very end of the checkout process.The new regulations, which are slated to take effect next year, seek to crack down on “bait and switch” pricing practices, according to FTC Chair Lina Khan, who said the agency has received a groundswell of complaints about service charges, amenity fees and a raft of other potentially obscure, last-minute additions to consumers’ bills. The FTC’s rules still allow companies to impose fees, so long as they are clearly displayed.The agency also focused its prohibition on just the lodging and live-event industries, not the fuller array of firms — from airlines to internet giants — that have similarly stoked public anger.

Young adults are far more likely to approve of Luigi Mangione. The pollster YouGov asked a battery of questions recently about the killing of UnitedHealthcare chief executive Brian Thompson in Manhattan two weeks ago and the man who has been charged for it, Luigi Mangione. (Mangione was charged Tuesday with murder and terrorism.) Many people appeared unfamiliar with the story, offering no opinions. But among those who did, lots of young adults appeared sympathetic toward the alleged killer. And notably, they perceived those around them as sharing such views. The poll, which surveyed more than 1,000 people, showed Americans adults under 30 are about evenly split on whether they view Mangione favorably or unfavorably. About one-third hold each view. Adults aged 30 to 44 leaned only slightly negatively toward him. (In contrast, Americans aged 65-plus viewed Mangione unfavorably by about a 15-to-1 margin. Overall, Americans viewed Mangione more than 2-to-1 negatively.) Younger adults actually viewed Mangione more favorably than the man he allegedly killed, Thompson. Caption from article by Aaron Blake.

Reality TV contestants may soon be employees. The National Labor Relations Board said this week that contestants on the show “Love Is Blind” are employees and should have the work protections that come with that classification. Once remedied, the case could become the basis for the improved working conditions that reality show stars have long awaited. After the agency worked with two “Love Is Blind” stars who filed unfair labor practice charges in 2023, the NLRB regional office in Minnesota assigned to the case issued a filing Wednesday. It said the hit Netflix show’s production companies — Delirium TV and Kinetic Content — had misclassified contestants as “non-employee ‘participants’” and found that they had required cast mates to sign participant agreements to discourage them from participating in legally protected labor actions, such as unionizing. The production companies and their former employees must come to an agreement on remedies due to the unlawful portions of the contract or meet for a hearing before an NLRB judge on April 22. Caption from original article by Samantha Chery.

A large number of mysterious drones have been reported flying over New Jersey and across the eastern U.S., sparking speculation and concern over where they came from and why. New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy and U.S. Sen. Andy Kim have both gone out on drone hunts, hoping for answers. The FBI, Homeland Security, state police and other agencies are investigating.

THIS Moon is Constantly ERUPTING No moon in our solar system is likely as chaotic as Io, Jupiter’s third largest. The rocky body looks like a pepperoni pizza because of the constant, numerous eruptions on its surface. The volcanic activity fills the skies with sulfur dioxide and is constantly changing features on the ground. It’s the most volcanically active world in our solar neighborhood, and has an impressive résumé for a place that is only slightly larger than our own moon.“Io is one of the most intriguing objects in the whole solar system,” said Scott Bolton, a director at the Southwest Research Institute. “This body is completely covered with volcanoes over both poles, all across its middle, constantly going off. So how does this really happen?” Io’s volcanic origins have baffled scientists. Many thought a global magma ocean may be percolating under Io’s surface, a feature that could have been common in the early evolution of planetary bodies in our universe and could explain the wide spread of volcanic activity.

voice_to_text: so for years we've been telling you all that Dasani has salt in it and people are like oh no it doesn't have salt in it what did you think that sodium Chloride was anyway I will still not be consuming this water and it's just the principle of the matter at this point because why why have you had salt in your water this whole time and you had salt in this water belligerently the Coca Cola Company who owns Dasani knows damn well that nobody is drinking this water and they have tried for how long to force it on us anyway you go to amusement parks sporting events concerts and apparently the only option always is Dasani I would rather drink out of a puddle and I know that I'm not alone in that feeling because anytime there's a Hurricane anytime there's some kind of a natural disaster or more preparing the Dasani is always left on the shelves anytime I go to the store every other water can be sold out the sun is always on the shelf so still I don't care if you took your salt out of the water I'm not drinking it because you've tried to assault us with this nasty water for this long telling me that your salty water tastes better when it really tastes like the bottom of a fish tank

video_description: Good luck to us all #banned #supremecourt #tiktokban #jobmarket #jobs #jobsearch #resume #businessowner #creator
voice_to_text: the job market if TikTok gets banned it's about to be so insane because people can already not find jobs and imagine now all the creators and the business owners on here that are literally going to have to enter the job market maybe they already work but they might need a second job or a third job to replace the money that they've made on TikTok TikTok is trying its hardest to appeal the law that they're trying to put in place by January 19th to ban TikTok in the United States and even though they appealed it with the US appeal courts they literally struck that down the law has been upheld and now it's going to the Supreme Court and the Supreme Court could also say listen we're upholding this and the ban is still going to be in effect and like I said in a job market where people cannot find jobs every job posting is getting two three four five hundred 1,000 2,000 applicants the minute it's posted people on here all the time talking about how they put in 1,000 2,000 3,000 job applications and they've gotten like 10 interviews and have not gotten a job what happens now to the economy what happens now when all of the people that are on this app that are creators and business owners have to flood into that market as well it's going to be a disaster

*[Yn: Versity যেতে যেতে তোমাদের কিছু বলি আসলে আমার বড় চাচা Jungkook ভাইয়ার বাবা আর বড় চাচি তার মা। ওরা সত্যিই অনেক ভালো, আমাকে ছোট থেকেই অনেক ভালো-বাসে। তবে আমার দাদী'টা কেমন জানি..!! বাবা মা'রা যাওয়ার পর কেমন জানি হয়ে গেছে..!! কিন্তু তবুও আমি তাকে অনেক সম্মান করি]* প্রায় ৪০ মিনিট হাটার পর অবশেষে সে তার গন্তব্য Versity তে পৌছে যায়। হাপাচ্ছে এখন খুব গরমও লাগছে। Yn 1st year এর ছাত্রী ছিলো বলে ও Varsity'r junior ছিলো। সিনিয়র'রা আজও অনেক Junior দের বু'লি করছে। তবে Yn এই ফাঁকে গেটের চিপায় ঢুকে ভিতিরে ঢুকে যেতে চেয়েছিলো ঠিক তখনই সামনে কয়েকটা সিনিয়র আসে। ??: তোর ফোন দে' নাহলে ভাৰ্ছিটি ঢুকতে দিবো না....!! Yn জানে কে এ...!! এক রাগী দৃষ্টিতে তাকায় ওর দিকে..!! Yn: কেনো..? তোের কী ফোন নেই..? ভাইয়া প্রতিদিন এসব ভালো লাগে না সর..!! আমাকে ঠিক মতো পড়তে দে..!! নিজেও পর..!! Jungkook: তোকে না বলছি আমাকে আপনি বলে ডাকতে..? বেশী করবি তো একদম বের করে দিবো..!! Yn: না দেবো না বলবোও না সর তুই..!! Yn Jungkook কে ধাক্কা দেয়ে পাশ কাটিয়ে চলে যায় এ দেখে জুংকুকের গ্রুপের জেনি বলে উঠে। জেনি: দেখেছিস মেয়েটার সাহস কত..? ও কিন্তু বেশী বেড়ে গেছে..!! জুংকুক: বাড়'তে দে ওকে..!! বাকি'টা ওকে আমি দেখে নিবো..!! Yn গিয়ে নিজের ব্যাগ ক্লাসে রেখে সোজা লাইব্রেরি তে চলে যায়। আজ সকাল থেকেই ওর অনেক গল্পের বই পড়তে ইচভহা করছে Yn নিজের মন মতো একটা বই নিয়ে পড়তে থাকে। Yn এর অনেক ভালো লাগছিলো। কিন্তু হয়তো Yn এর ভালো লাগা অন্য একটি ব্যাক্তির সহ্য হচ্ছে না। ব্যাক্তিটি কেউ না জুংকুক। হঠাৎ পিছন থেকে জুংকুক এসে yn এর হাত থেকে বইটা নিয়ে তার ভিতর থেকে কত-গুলো পৃষ্টা ছি'ড়ে ফেলে। Yn: ভাইয়া.......!! এইটা কী করলি তুই...? জুংকুক: আমি আবার কী করলাম..? যা করলি তা তো তুই-ই করলি...!! Yn: আমি তো কিছু'ই করলাম না..!! বরং তুই'ই বইটা ছি'ড়ে দিলি...!! এখন আমার দোষ দিচ্ছিস কেনো? লাইবেরিয়ান এইদিকেই আসছিলো তাই Jungkook কৌশলে Yn এর হাতে ছে'ড়া বই আর ছে'ড়া পৃষ্টা গুলো দেয়। এমন ভাব নেয় যেনো কিচ্ছু করে নি..!! লাইবেরিয়ান একসাথে এতো গুলো মানুষ দেখে এখানে আসে। এসেই দেখে Yn এর হাতে ছে'ড়া বই..!! দেখেই যেনো চ'টে যায়। ??-: এই মেয়ে তুমি বই ছি'ড়েছো কেনো..? বই পড়ার জন্য খেলার জন্য নয়..!! Yn: sir...!! আমি এইটা ছি'ড়ি নি Jungkook ভাইয়া ছি'ড়েছে..!! ও~~ই..!! Yn এর কথা বলার সুযোগ দেওয়ার আগেই জুংকুকের গ্রুপের জেনি বলে উঠে----> জেনি: স্যার...!! মিথ্যা বলছে ও..!! এই দেখুন আমি সাক্ষি এই কাজটা এই মেয়েটাই করেছে..!! জেনির মতো Jungkook এর সহ-পাঠি সবাই মিলে Yn এর না করা কাজে'র উপর সাক্ষি দিচ্ছিলো..!! ??-: এখনও কী বলবে? তুমি এই কাজ'টি করো নি..? Yn: স্যার~~!! আমি সত্যিই এই কাজটি করি নি..!! ??-: চুপ একদম চুপ..!! যা বোঝার তা বুঝে গেছি..!! আজকে তুমি ক্লাস করতে পারবে না আর না-হয় এই বইয়ের বাবদ ৫০০ টাকা দেওয়া লাগবে। Yn: স্যার, কাজটা Jungkook ভাইয়া করেছে আমি না.. ??-: এতো গুলো Student এর কথা মিথ্যা হতে পারে না কখনও...!! যাই-হোক তোমার পথ ২ টাই বইয়ের জন্য টাকা দিবে আর না-হয় ক্লাস করতে পারবে না আজ..!! Yn: আচ্ছা...!! এই নিন..!! Yn তার ফোনের ব্যাক' কভার থেকে ৫০০ টাকা বেড় করে স্যার'কে দিয়ে দেয়। Yn: সরি স্যার...!! আসলে কিছু কিছু মানুষ আছে যারা সময়ের সঙে পালটে যায় বাতাসের গতিতে..!! তবে আমি এর জন্য অনুশোচনা করি না...!! আপনাকেও ধন্যবাদ এতো বড় ভুলকে সত্যি করে দেখার জন্য..!! ভালো থাকবেন..!! Yn আর কিছু বলে না সেখান থেকে সোজা চলে আসে ক্লাস রুমে। আর ওইদিকে Sir Yn এর কথার কিছু বোঝে না তার বুঝেও লাভ নেই নিজের কক্ষে ফিরে যায় উনি। জুংকুক তার ফ্রেন্ডদের নিয়ে বাইরে যায়। আর Yn নিজের ক্লাসে এসে চুপচাপ বসে আছে। একদম পিছনের সিটটা ওর...!! কারো সাথে বন্ধুত্বও নেই। Yn: ভাইয়া তুইও সবার মতো পালটে গেলি..!! আমাকে তুই আগে আগলে রাখতি আর এখন--? আমার সাথে সব-সময়ই খারাপ' ব্যবহার করিস..!! তোের একা করলে চলে না হাজার জনকে নিয়েও করিস..!! হয়তো এইটাইয়া আমার কপালে লিখা ছিলো..!! (মনে মনে) টেবিলে উপর হাত ভাজ করে তার উপর মাথা দিয়ে জানালা'র দিকে তাকিয়ে কথা গুলো মনে মনে বলছে Yn আর জুংকুক ওর ফ্রেন্ডদের নিয়ে মজায় ব্যাস্ত। তো অনেক সময় কেটে যায় ক্লাস শেষ হয়ে যায়। #cousins_bully  #bts #jungkook #ff #btsstory #btsarmy #fyppp #foryou #followers #viral #tiktok

voice_to_text: Merry Christmas get up no seriously get up it's four in the morning we have a lot of videos to make today we're gonna pretend like we're sleeping and then when you hear this phone beep three times you're gonna run in and wake us up okay you guys should be waking us up now all right you guys lots of excitement as we go downstairs to see what Santa left make it look magical no no go back go back why are you pouting now we have to redo it our kids obviously know the true meaning of Christmas but this year we decided to spoil them and we bought over 1,000 presents for them to open I know some of you guys are gonna say it’s for the clickbait  but it's not we actually just love our kids show me your best thumbnail face let's see it wait do not open anything you guys all right Mommy and daddy didn’t just buy all these presents so you guys can open them all Hannah Grace did Santa put pads in your stocking Hold them up so I can see them Don’t throw them Your gonna need them your becoming a woman  Hannah Grace threw one of her gifts because she was upset with what she got Which is not okay so ultimately we had to make the tough decision  To take away all of her presents which was really hard but you know parenting doesn't stop just because it's the holidays and she needs to learn to be more grateful so tomorrow daddy will be going live while he takes her to donate all of her presents to poor people I know you guys are all enjoying your presents but daddy and I have one more surprise for you look listen look at the camera You’re gonna have a new baby sister it's true we're pregnant with our 8th little So get ready for more baby bath routine videos in the future She’s gonna make us so much money

voice_to_text: what's up you guys I want you to check out this deal I'm about to talk about it's worth your time I promise you're gonna love it check it out I used to be really really identified with my anxiety it ruled all of my decisions the way I felt everything leading to me having a drinking problem now I have been doing somatic therapy dance movement therapy for the last few years dance movement therapy has been the most important part of my healing journey because learning that your brain just distracts you from what's happening in your body because when you had whatever trauma happened to you it was unsafe to feel the feelings in your body therefore the mind distracts you from what's happening in your body so getting in touch with your body and approaching it with compassion and care will help you heal so what I wanted to do was I wanted to give people affordable ways to get in touch with their body and that's where healing and body comes in so I had a meeting with Chelsea Healing and body and she really wanted to bring this to people as well they have a bunch of digestible affordable videos to get you in touch with your body to help you to start healing from anxiety depression OCD whatever they also have a get out of your mind course that you can take it's usually $222 and they are selling it right now for a hundred bucks with the code jewels J U L E s all caps they have forever changed my life and so many others with having compassion for themselves because trauma isn't our fault but it is our responsibility to heal it and as hard as that is it's so worth it
